Where modern C++ IS enough (no external libs)
You do NOT need external libs for:

    âœ… Data structures
    âœ… Algorithms
    âœ… Multithreading (std::thread, mutex)
    âœ… File I/O
    âœ… Memory management
    âœ… RAII
    âœ… Generic programming
    âœ… Performance-critical core logic
    âœ… System-level engines
    âœ… Embedded logic

This is why in HFT, OS, DB engines, compilers, the core is pure C++, and libs are used only at the edges.

Mental model (important)
    C++ standard    = language + core tools
    Libraries       = domain power

Modern C++ is strong at â€œhowâ€ things work, not â€œwhatâ€ domain you work in.
For anything beyond CPU + memory + files â†’ external libs are normal and expected.

